column50: Carcasses mainly predated dead on banks, some senescent in stream covered in silty clay.
column51: Ended count at 250m after 2 consequetive reaches with no fish observed.

column49: Some dark pools but stream level and visibility good overall. Small section earound logjam and dark pools above and below not visible.
column50: Most carcasses observed were predated, senescent carcasses likely washed out of stream during recent high flow.
column51: High flow in recent days, we tried to count it on Oct 15 but it was too fast flowing.

column49: Fish visible and eadily countable in estuary and lower reaches. Some dark pools in upper reaches, and dark in the cave, made it harder to see in those sections, but still a good count.
column50: Many predated carcasses on banks.
column51: Shares long estuary with Beales Right, shared portion attributed here to Beales Left. Pinks observed on redds in upper estuary, so recorded as spawning in estuary.

column49: Good count or Right estuary and first reach, medium countability in second reach, uncountable after 100m due to fast/high water.
column50: Predated carcasses observed on banks.
column51: Shared estuary attributed to Beales Left count, right estuary (~100m after fork with Beales Left) included here. Ended count at 100m due to fast water (difficult to walk in stream, and no banks) and low visibility. Fairly normal conditions for upper reaches.

column49: Very reliable count of estuary and first 100m, but did not complete the stream count. Water level and colour and tide made for excellent visibility in estuary/stream.
column50: Thorough count of estuary and first 100m.
column51: *PARTIAL COUNT* Ended count after 100m due to strong outflow winds. Slow counting dead in estuary with only 2 counters. LOTS of bear kills with only the head remaining, bears eating entire kill instead of being choosy? Several bald eagles, ravens, crows, and gulls observed scavenging in the estuary.

column49: No live fish observed in estuary, stream, or holding in bay.
column50: Thorough search in and on immediate banks of stream for carcasses, though some could have been dragged away by bears.
column51: All fish observed were bear kills, mostly consumed. Senescent may have washed out. Bald eagle seen drying off on the ground next to stream. Lots of bear sign (scat, predated carcasses, dug up rocks, broken branches, chewed flagging).
